  "prompt": "How easy is it to submit a question on Quora?",
  "response": "Submitting a question on Quora is generally quite easy and straightforward. Here's a step-by-step guide:\n\n1. **Sign In:** If you don't have an account, you'll need to sign up. You can sign in using your email address, Google account, or Facebook account.\n\n2. **Question Submission:**\n    - Go to the Quora homepage.\n    - Look for the \"Ask Question\" button, usually located at the top of the page.\n    - Click on this button, and a pop-up or new page will appear where you can type in your question.\n\n3. **Formulate Your Question:**\n    - Make sure your question is clear and specific.\n    - Quora often suggests potential improvements to the phrasing or grammar of your question.\n\n4. **Add Follow-Up Details (Optional):**\n    - You can provide additional context or details to make your question easier to understand.\n    - Tags or topics can be added to categorize your question and increase visibility.\n\n5. **Submit:**\n    - Once you're satisfied with your question, click the \"Add Question\" or \"Submit\" button.\n\n6. **Feedback and Edits:**\n    - After submission, Quora's community or moderation team might suggest edits to refine your question.\n    - You can accept or reject these suggestions.\n\nOverall, the process is designed to be user-friendly, ensuring that even new users can submit questions without much hassle.",
